figure at the center—someone who sets
things in motion and holds the key to
how the story unfolds—Patient Zero. This
hour, Radiolab hunts for Patient Zeroes
of all kinds and considers the course of
an ongoing outbreak...

Radiolab is a show about curiosity. Where sound
illuminates ideas, and the boundaries blur be
tween science, philosophy, and human experi
ence.
Radiolab is heard around the country on more
than 450 NPR member stations. Check your local
station for airtimes.
Radiolab is supported, in part, by the National Science
Foundation and the Alfred P. Sloan Foundation, enhanc
ing public understanding of science and technology in
the modern world. More information about Sloan at
www.sloan.org.
